History of Computing.
Origins, key milestones, key people, future directions.
Long, detailed essay.

    *   *Introduction:* Define computing (not just electronic), the scope of the essay, and the thesis (computing is a journey from mechanical tools to abstract intelligence).
    *   *Pre-Electronic Era (Origins):* Abacus, mechanical calculators (Pascal, Leibniz), Babbage's engines (Difference/Analytical), Ada Lovelace (the first programmer).
    *   *The Birth of Electronic Computing (WWII & Early Mainframes):* Turing (Turing Machine/Enigma), ENIAC, Von Neumann architecture, transistors replacing vacuum tubes.
    *   *The Microprocessor Revolution (Personal Computing):* Integrated circuits, Moore's Law, Intel, Apple/Microsoft era, the GUI.
    *   *The Internet and Connectivity Era:* ARPANET, TCP/IP, the World Wide Web (Berners-Lee), mobile computing.
    *   *The Modern Era (Data & AI):* Cloud computing, Big Data, Machine Learning, Deep Learning.
    *   *Future Directions:* Quantum computing, Neuromorphic computing, AI singularity/AGI, Bio-computing

